[src:data-flow-analysis/def-use-chain] In general, a declaration of a variable can be in an outer scope (e.g., a global variable).
[src:data-flow-analysis/def-use-chain] When a variable, *v*, is on the LHS of an assignment statement, such as ⁠ $s(j)$ ⁠, then ⁠ $s(j)$ ⁠ is a definition of *v*.
[src:data-flow-analysis/def-use-chain] Every variable (*v*) has at least one definition by its declaration (*V*) (or initialization).
